### Feature 1 — Login Attempt Counter Display
**Skill: Reading from session, passing data to view**

Currently the system blocks after 5 attempts but doesn't tell the user how many attempts are left.

Add this to `loadHomePage()` when login fails:

```java
if (users == null) {
    userLoginAttemptService.loginFailed(userModel.getEmailId());
    
    // NEW: calculate remaining attempts
    int attempts = userLoginAttemptService.getAttemptCount(userModel.getEmailId());
    int remaining = LoginController.MAX_ATTEMPT - attempts;
    
    if (remaining > 0) {
        model.put("message", "Invalid credentials. " + remaining + " attempts remaining.");
    } else {
        model.put("AlreadyLoggedInError", "Account locked for 5 minutes.");
    }
    return "redirect:login";
}
```

**What you learn:** Session data, business logic, user feedback.

