### Feature 3 — New AJAX Endpoint
**Skill: Writing REST-style endpoints, returning JSON**

Add a new endpoint that checks if a username already exists during registration:

```java
@RequestMapping(value = "/checkUsernameAvailable", method = RequestMethod.POST)
public @ResponseBody Map<String, Object> checkUsernameAvailable(
        @RequestParam String username) {

    Map<String, Object> map = new HashMap<String, Object>();
    try {
        Users existing = (Users) commonService.fetchObjectByNamedQuery(
            "findUserByUsername", "usmUserName=" + username + "=string");

        if (existing != null) {
            map.put("available", false);
            map.put("message", "Username already taken");
        } else {
            map.put("available", true);
            map.put("message", "Username available");
        }
    } catch (Exception e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
        map.put("available", false);
        map.put("message", "Error checking username");
    }
    return map;
}
```

**What you learn:** `@RequestParam`, `@ResponseBody`, JSON response structure, named queries.

