### Feature 4 — Password Strength Validation
**Skill: String operations, business logic, validation**

In `resetPassword()`, before saving the new password, validate it:

```java
@RequestMapping(value = "/resetPassword", method = RequestMethod.POST)
public @ResponseBody Map<String, Object> resetPassword(
        @ModelAttribute UserModel userModel, HttpSession session) {

    Map<String, Object> map = new HashMap<String, Object>();
    try {
        String newPassword = userModel.getConfirmPassword();

        // NEW: Password validation
        if (newPassword == null || newPassword.length() < 8) {
            map.put("flag", false);
            map.put("message", "Password must be at least 8 characters");
            return map;
        }
        if (!newPassword.matches(".*[A-Z].*")) {
            map.put("flag", false);
            map.put("message", "Password must contain at least one uppercase letter");
            return map;
        }
        if (!newPassword.matches(".*[0-9].*")) {
            map.put("flag", false);
            map.put("message", "Password must contain at least one number");
            return map;
        }

        // existing save logic...
        CitizenMaster citizenMaster = (CitizenMaster) commonService
                .findById(CitizenMaster.class, userModel.getCitizenId());
        // ...

    } catch (Exception e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
    }
    return map;
}
```

**What you learn:** String `.matches()` with regex, early return pattern, layered validation.

