## Stage 5 — Learn the Concepts Behind What You're Using (Ongoing)

### For each thing you use in the project, learn the concept behind it

| You use this in the project | Learn this concept |
|---|---|
| `@Transactional` | ACID properties, database transactions, rollback |
| `commonService.findById()` | JPA EntityManager, Hibernate session |
| `session.setAttribute()` | HTTP session, stateless vs stateful, cookies |
| `@Autowired` | Dependency Injection, IoC container, Spring beans |
| `List<Object[]>` from native queries | JDBC ResultSet, how Hibernate maps raw SQL |
| `ModelAndView` | MVC pattern, request-response cycle |
| `@RequestMapping` | HTTP methods (GET/POST), URL routing |
| `try-catch` | Exception hierarchy, checked vs unchecked exceptions |
| `HashMap` | Hash table data structure, time complexity O(1) |
| `Serializable` | Java serialization, object streams |

**How to learn each one:**
1. Google: "Spring @Transactional explained simply"
2. Read for 15 minutes
3. Find where it's used in your project
4. Write one sentence explaining it in your own words

